Terraform, Cilium, until we can get `kubectl` online.


<https://docs.siderolabs.com/talos/v1.12/platform-specific-installations/virtualized-platforms/proxmox>

Need to have a special image with `qemu-guest-agent` support.

<https://factory.talos.dev/>

`https://factory.talos.dev/image/ce4c980550dd2ab1b17bbf2b08801c7eb59418eafe8f279833297925d67c7515/v1.12.5/metal-amd64.iso`

talos terraform provider, but the documentation isn't particularly helpful.
Found these examples: <https://github.com/siderolabs/terraform-provider-talos/tree/main/examples>
and this blog post: <https://olav.ninja/talos-cluster-on-proxmox-with-terraform>

How to list config of an already existing node?

```
pvesh get /nodes/dorne/qemu/105/config
```

Failed test:

```
resource "proxmox_virtual_environment_vm" "talos_cp1" {
  name        = "talos-cp1-test"
  description = "Managed by Terraform"
  tags        = ["terraform", "talos"]
  node_name   = var.proxmox_node_name
  on_boot     = true

  agent {
    enabled = true
  }

  cpu {
    cores = 4
    type = "x86-64-v2-AES"
  }

  memory {
    dedicated = 4096
    floating = 4096
  }

  network_device {
    bridge = "vmbr0"
  }

  disk {
    datastore_id = "local-lvm"
    file_id = proxmox_virtual_environment_download_file.talos_image.id
    file_format = "raw"
    interface = "scsi0"
    size = 20
    ssd = true
  }

  operating_system {
    type = "l26"
  }

  initialization {
    datastore_id = "local-lvm"
    ip_config {
      ipv4 {
        address = "${var.talos_cp1_ip}/24"
        gateway = var.default_gateway
      }
    }
  }
}
```

