Update from proxmox 8 -> 9.1.6

<https://github.com/rgl/terraform-proxmox-talos/blob/main/talos.tf>

# Bootstap


```
terraform apply
just init_cluster_config

# Nodes will not be ready
# Gateway CRDs need to exist before we install cilium
kubectl apply -f https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/gateway-api/releases/download/v1.2.1/standard-install.yaml
helm install cilium cilium/cilium \
  --namespace kube-system \
  --version 1.19.2 \
  --set kubeProxyReplacement=true \
  --set k8sServiceHost=10.1.4.100 \
  --set k8sServicePort=6443 \
  --set l2announcements.enabled=true \
  --set externalIPs.enabled=true \
  --set gatewayAPI.enabled=true \
  --set ipam.mode=kubernetes \
  --set operator.replicas=1 \
  --set securityContext.privileged=true

# Need to wait until done
kubectl rollout status daemonset/cilium -n kube-system
# Then we can do
kubectl apply -f gitops/bootstrap/cilium_config.yaml
# Nodes will now become healthy
talosctl -n 10.1.4.10 health

helm repo add argo https://argoproj.github.io/argo-helm
helm repo update
helm install argocd argo/argo-cd -n argocd --create-namespace --version 9.4.16 \
  --set server.service.type=LoadBalancer \
  --set server.service.annotations."io\.cilium/lb-ipam-ips"=10.1.4.102
# See ip
kubectl get svc argocd-server -n argocd
argocd admin initial-password -n argocd
# Username `admin`
argocd login 10.1.4.102 --insecure
argocd account update-password
argocd repo add https://git.hietala.xyz/tree/home-ops.git --username admin --password <token>
```

# New bootstrap with cilium

```
terraform apply
```

`talosctl -n 10.1.4.10 health` will stop at:

```
waiting for all k8s nodes to report ready: ...
waiting for all k8s nodes to report ready: some nodes are not ready: [talos-cp1 talos-cp2 talos-cp3]
```

Should install gateway API before installing cilium:

```
kubectl apply -f https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/gateway-api/releases/download/v1.2.1/standard-install.yaml
```

Now install cilium:

```
helm install cilium cilium/cilium \
  --namespace kube-system \
  --version 1.17.2 \
  --set kubeProxyReplacement=true \
  --set k8sServiceHost=10.1.4.100 \
  --set k8sServicePort=6443 \
  --set l2announcements.enabled=true \
  --set externalIPs.enabled=true \
  --set gatewayAPI.enabled=true \
  --set ipam.mode=kubernetes \
  --set operator.replicas=1
  --set securityContext.privileged=true
```

```
kubectl apply -f gitops/apps/cilium_config.yaml
```

Needed to work with Talos:

```yaml
securityContext:
  privileged: true
```

Can test with nginx, should work properly.

Then setup argocd as before

For the impatiant:

```
kubectl annotate applications -n argocd --all argocd.argoproj.io/refresh=hard
```

